1299.24 1016.15 Td
(A note about Serial B: THE TXD LINES DON'T SUPPORT DIFFERENTIAL OPERATION!) Tj
T* (Serial B can operate in 2 modes: differential \(RS-422\) and single-ended \(RS-232\). ) Tj
T* (But we can't do differential because I couldn't find a modern line driver IC that could be switched between differential and single-ended on the fly like the Lisa requires.) Tj
T* (So I instead used a single-ended IC drivers since you'll be using the port in RS-232 mode 99 times out of 100 anyway.) Tj
T* (The RXD lines do still support differential mode though, so at least you can receive differential data!) Tj
